Lotus has unveiled its latest hypercar, the Evija, which is an all-electric vehicle that can fast charge to 100% battery in just 9 minutes. The car boasts 2000PS (around 1,973 horsepower), which Lotus claims makes the vehicle the “most powerful car ever to enter production”. It boasts a top speed of over 320km/h and a range of 400km – making it a competitor to Tesla’s Roadster. It is significantly more expensive than the Roadster, however, costing $2.1 million (R29.37 million). Lotus CEO Phil Popham said that the Evija would re-establish the Lotus brand in the hearts and minds of sports car fans. Photos of the Evija are below. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-313577" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-2-573x430.jpg" alt="lotus-2" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-2-573x430.jpg 573w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-2-533x400.jpg 533w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-2-1200x900.jpg 1200w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-2.jpg 1333w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-313569" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-3-573x430.jpg" alt="lotus-3" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-3-573x430.jpg 573w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-3-533x400.jpg 533w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-3-768x576.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-3-1200x900.jpg 1200w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/lotus-3.jpg 1333w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984p